ballet /ˈbæleɪ/

(ballets) 

1. N-UNCOUNT Ballet is a type of very skilled and artistic dancing with carefully planned movements. 芭蕾舞 [also 'the' N, oft N n] 

例： I trained as a ballet dancer. 我受过做芭蕾舞演员的训练。 

2. N-COUNT A ballet is an artistic work that is performed by ballet dancers. 芭蕾舞剧 

例： The performance will include the premiere of three new ballets. 这次演出将包括3部新芭蕾舞剧的首演。

